In a truth revealing moment, Victoria has proven she is an all-round posh woman as she reveals she spends almost £6 on bread for her simple avocado and toast breakfast. Taking to Instagram, the former Spice Girl, 45, shared a snap of the healthy breakfast staple made with bible inspired wholegrain Ezekiel 4:9 bread and admitted her children love it in a report by Dail Mail. The loaf, made from sprouted grains, is only available from Amazon’s grocery store in the United Kingdom and takes its name from the Hebrew prophet, a central protagonist in the Book of Ezekiel. Created by health food company Food For Life, Ezekiel products are also developed in accordance with Holy Scripture verse Ezekiel 4:9 <img class="aligncenter wp-image-1094431 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/23420576-7889423-image-m-2_1579076110529-357x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="2144" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/23420576-7889423-image-m-2_1579076110529-357x598.jpg 357w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/23420576-7889423-image-m-2_1579076110529-333x557.jpg 333w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/23420576-7889423-image-m-2_1579076110529-143x240.jpg 143w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/23420576-7889423-image-m-2_1579076110529-287x480.jpg 287w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/23420576-7889423-image-m-2_1579076110529-358x600.jpg 358w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/23420576-7889423-image-m-2_1579076110529.jpg 634w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> The passage reads: ‘Take also unto thee wheat, and barley, and beans, and lentils and millet, and spelt and put them in one vessel.’ The high price is understood to be based on its inflated labour costs, caused by its use of sprouted grains and pulses. You buy at close to £6 and delivery is a bit more than £2 It is also is developed without the use of flour, genetically modified organisms and refined sugars While it retails at a significantly higher price than the standard loaf, Ezekiel has a series of nutritional benefits, including an increase in vitamins B1, B2, and vitamin E.